At that part of the game for me the plan for white should be to push the queen's pawns as far as it possible and so my plan was to prevent that. So I continue to attack the a pawn
{My engine suggests 32. Nf6 instead, but I find f5 more convincing. Keeping the position closed just increases the potence of the knight and the white queenside pawns are no danger. If I hadn't given away material earlier, this move would produce tactical possibilities for an exchange sacrifice. But with a minor piece up, keeping the positon closed with mutual positional weaknesses is just the way to go.}
